Package spoon.reflect.code

Interface CtLiteral<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of literal's value
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, CtCodeElement, CtElement, CtExpression<T>, CtQueryable, CtTypedElement<T>, CtVisitable, FactoryAccessor, java.io.Serializable, SourcePositionHolder, TemplateParameter<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CtTextBlock
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CtLiteralImpl, CtTextBlockImpl
    public interface CtLiteral<T>
extends CtExpression<T>
    This code element defines a literal value (an int, a string, etc). 
         int x = 4; // 4 is a literal
    A null literal, as in s = null", is represented by a CtLiteral whose value is null.
